## Installing Linux (Ubuntu)
#

## Download
1. Download Ubuntu iso image from official website.

Note - Try installing LTS version (LTS = Long Term Support)
URL  - https://ubuntu.com/download

## Create Bootable USB
2. Create a bootable usb using any trusted application like Rufus

## Persistence
3. Persistence space is used to store any work you do while running linux from usb.

-----------------------------------------------------------------
------- Common commands to run regularly ------------------------
-----------------------------------------------------------------

$ sudo apt update
$ sudo apt upgrade
# or
$ sudo apt upgrade -y  # choose yes to every prompt


------------------------------------------------------------------
-------- How to install VS Code in Linux -------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------

## Installation command
$ sudo snap install --classic code

## Run VS Code
$ code

## uninstall VS Code
$ sudo snap remove code

